getDevicesStatesHistoryAsString

public java.lang.String getDevicesStatesHistoryAsString(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> devicesID,
                                                        java.lang.String propertyName,
                                                        long time_start,
                                                        long time_end)
Simple getter for property changes on the Database

Specified by:
getDevicesStatesHistoryAsString in interface PropertyHistoryManager
Parameters:
devicesID - is an Array of devicesID (String) on which we want to evaluate the property name, if null, we inspect all devices ID
propertyName - The property name to evaluate
time_start - is the difference, measured in milliseconds, between the desired STARTING period and midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC, (not that simulated values, as future values can lead to weird results, loss of causality)
time_end - is the difference, measured in milliseconds, between the desired ENDING period and midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC, maximum value 'should' be the current Time (except for simulation -> which can lead to weird results, loss of causality), time_end value MUST be greater than time_start
Returns:
a String that represent DB results as a JSON Array (itself containing Arrays), example : [ deviceID1 : [{time: time_start, state: v0},{time:t1,state:v1},...,{time:tf,state:vf} ], deviceID2 : [...], ... ]

getDevicesStatesHistoryAsJSON

public org.json.JSONObject getDevicesStatesHistoryAsJSON(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> devicesID,
                                                         java.lang.String propertyName,
                                                         long time_start,
                                                         long time_end)
Specified by:
getDevicesStatesHistoryAsJSON in interface PropertyHistoryManager
Returns:
Directly the JSON Object (each deviceId is associated with a JSONArray), example : { "deviceID1":[{"time":time_start,"value":"v0"},{"time":t1,"value":"v1"},...,{"time":tn,"value":"vn"} ], "deviceID2":[...], ... }
